rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated as part of the process of building the software to create a releasable artifact (e.g., executable or package) from data such as source files, dependencies, built components, build process ephemeral data, and other SBOMs.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element doesn't fit into any of the other categories

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: riskAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a risk assessment for a package.
Identifies an Element to be referenced by other Elements.
Refers to any unit of content that can be associated with a distribution of software.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing a set of licensing information where all elements apply.
Defines the beginning of a range.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: numeric
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists only of numeric entries.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: availableFrom
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is available from the additional supplier described by each `to` Element
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition, in SPDX templating format.
A license that is not listed on the SPDX License List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amendedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is amended by each `to` Element
A mathematically calculated representation of a grouping of data.
The name of a relevant standard that may apply to an artifact.
An assertion made in relation to one or more elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: text
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists of unstructured text, such as a book, wikipedia article (without images), or transcript.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single or a collection of source files
Designates elements as products where the impact of a vulnerability is being investigated.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: invokedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element was invoked by the `to` Agent during a LifecycleScopeType period (for example, a Build element that describes a build step)
A license exception that is listed on the SPDX Exceptions list.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssociatedVulnerability
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Used to associate a `from` Artifact with each `to` Vulnerability
Provides information about the primary purpose of an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directDownload
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fixedIn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) A `from` Vulnerability has been fixed in each of the `to` Element(s)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: purchaseOrder
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a purchase order for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Other exploit catalogs
An Individual Value for License where the SPDX data creator determines that no license is present.

Specifies an AI package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when the type doesn't match any of the other options.
Specifies whether the License is listed as approved by the [Open Source Initiative (OSI)](https://opensource.org).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDocumentation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element
A license expression participating in a license set.
A key with an associated value.
An individual human being.
Describes the confidentiality level of the data points contained in the dataset.
Agent represents anything with the potential to act on a system.
Base domain class from which all other SPDX-3.0 domain classes derive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: license
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional license information related to an artifact.
A license or addition that is not listed on the SPDX License List.
Class that describes a build instance of software/artifacts.
Identifies from where or whom the Element originally came.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasProvidedDependency
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a dependency on each `to` Element, but dependency is not in the distributed artifact, but assumed to be provided, during a LifecycleScopeType period

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metrics
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to metrics related to package such as OpenSSF scorecards.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data points in the dataset can be shared only with specific organizations and their clients on a need to know basis.
A probability score between 0 and 1 of a vulnerability being exploited.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandsTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` archive expands out as an artifact described by each `to` Element
Provides the location of an exploit catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to related security information of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityPolicy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to instructions for reporting newly discovered security vulnerabilities for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exportControlAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a export control assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasInputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build has each `to` Elements as an input during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseHistory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a published list of releases for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is related to the `from` Element where the relationship type is not described by any of the SPDX relationhip types (this relationship is directionless)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: audio
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is audio based, such as a collection of music from the 80s.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serializedInArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` SPDXDocument can be found in a serialized form in each `to` Artifact

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The third-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
Information about the relationship between two Elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: fixedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability has been fixed by the `to` Agent(s)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_384

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: altDownloadLocation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an alternative download location.
Specifies a data package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: review
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when someone reviews the Element.
An element of hardware and/or software utilized to carry out a particular function.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandedLicensing
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the expanded Licensing profile specification
A string in the license expression format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: sha3 with a digest length of 512 https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.202.pdf

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: manifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software manifest
Provide context for a relationship that occurs in the lifecycle.
Describes if any sensitive personal information is present in the dataset.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is no support for the artifact from the supplier, consumer assumes any support obligations.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: data
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is data
Provides a numerical (0-10) representation of the severity of a vulnerability.
Provides an exploit assessment of a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: firmware
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element provides low level control over a device's hardware
A reference to a resource outside the scope of SPDX-3.0 content that uniquely identifies an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 4 - 6.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: inlineMitigationsAlreadyExist
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Built-in inline controls or mitigations prevent an adversary from leveraging the vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: attend
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The vulnerability requires attention from the organization's internal, supervisory-level individuals. Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, and may involve publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. CISA recommends remediating Attend vulnerabilities sooner than standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: model
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a machine learning or artificial intelligence model
Describes one a profile which the creator of this ElementCollection intends to conform to.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sensor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: privacyAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a privacy assessment for a package.
Identifies the tooling that was used during the creation of the Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: No assertion can be made about the completeness of the relationship.
Describes all the preprocessing steps applied to the training data before the model training.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: syntactic
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data describes the syntax or semantics of a language or text, such as a parse tree used for natural language processing.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: testedOn
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (AI, Dataset) The `from` Element has been tested on the `to` Element
Enumeration of the different kinds of SPDX file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kev
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerability (KEV) Catalog

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: issueTracker
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the issue tracker for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityExploitabilityAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Exploitability eXchange (VEX) statement which provides information on whether a product is impacted by a specific vulnerability in an included package and, if affected, whether there are actions recommended to remediate. See also [NTIA VEX one-page](https://ntia.gov/files/ntia/publications/vex_one-page_summary.pdf).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: republishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by a `to` Agent(s)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: socialMedia
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a social media channel for a package.
The result of applying a hash algorithm to an Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: analyzed
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM generated through analysis of artifacts (e.g., executables, packages, containers, and virtual machine images) after its build. Such analysis generally requires a variety of heuristics. In some contexts, this may also be referred to as a 3rd party SBOM.
Connects a vulnerability and an element designating the element as a product affected by the vulnerability.
Specifies the SSVC decision type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: dataset
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Dataset profile specification
A tuple of two positive integers that define a range.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: copiedTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has been copied to each `to` Element
Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: staticAnalysisReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a static analysis report for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: modifiedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is modified by each `to` Element
An Individual Value for License when no assertion can be made about its actual value.
Describes relevant information about different steps of the training process.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vcs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a version control system related to a software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: blake2b algorithm with a digest size of 512 https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7693#section-4

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is metadata about the `from` Element (`from` hasMetadata `to`)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDependencyManifest
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has manifest files that contain dependency information in each `to` Element

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc3174

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF)](https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/2023-04/secure-software-self-attestation_common-form_508.pdf).
A container for a grouping of SPDX-3.0 content characterizing details (provenence, composition, licensing, etc.) about a product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deviceDriver

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: executable
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Element is an Artifact that can be run on a computer

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_224

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during the execution phase of an element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contains
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element contains each `to` Element

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOutputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build element generates each `to` Element as an output during a LifecycleScopeType period.
A license that is listed on the SPDX License List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityFix
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the patch or source code that fixes a vulnerability.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasConcludedLicense
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Software Artifact is concluded by the SPDX data creator to be governed by each `to` license

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerableCodeNotInExecutePath
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The affected code is not reachable through the execution of the code, including non-anticipated states of the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: sha3 with a digest length of 256 https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.202.pdf

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a disk image that can be written to a disk, booted in a VM, etc. A disk image typically contains most or all of the components necessary to boot, such as bootloaders, kernels, firmware, userspace, etc.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known to be exhaustive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: usesTool
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element uses each `to` Element as a tool during a LifecycleScopeType period.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when there is a security related identifier of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: core
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Core profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Track* in the SSVC spec) The vulnerability contains specific characteristics that may require closer monitoring for changes. CISA recommends remediating Track* vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: coordinatedBy

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 0 - 3.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: endOfSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is a defined end of support for the artifact from the supplier. This may also be referred to as end of life. There is a validUntilDate that can be used to signal when support ends for the artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: secure hashing algorithm with a digest length of 512 https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4634

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Build profile specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: secure hashing algorithm with a digest length of 256 https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4634

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The software is not affected because the vulnerable component is not in the product.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md2

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: critical

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to the mailing list used by the maintainer for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: support

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: no

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: usage

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtimeAnalysisReport

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: When a CVSS score is between 7.0 - 8.9

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during development phase of an element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseNotes

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: device
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element refers to a chipset, processor, or electronic board

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid Gitoid stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects) and a gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent the software [Artifact ID](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-id) or the [OmniBOR Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [OmniBOR Document](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#omnibor-document); this ambiguity exists because the OmniBOR Document is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Omnibor is a minimalistic schema to describe software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/main/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg). Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's ContentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the OmniBOR Document (OmniBOR Identifiers) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's ExternalIdentifier property.
